body:
Hello,

I have been getting an `EXC_BREAKPOINT` crash when handling external KVS updates on `com.apple.kvs.client.callback` queue. While this was happening rarely before, now it crashes consistently after every external update.

I have replaced selector-based notification with async stream which fixed the issue:

```swift
// Instead of:
NotificationCenter.default.addObserver(
    self,
    selector: #selector(didChangeExternally(notification:)),
    name: NSUbiquitousKeyValueStore.didChangeExternallyNotification,
    object: nil
)

// Using:
Task { @MainActor in
    for await notification in NotificationCenter.default.notifications(named: NSUbiquitousKeyValueStore.didChangeExternallyNotification) {
        didChangeExternally(notification: notification)
    }
}
```

It can also be fixed using a block-based observer and manually switching to the MainActor context. This approach is probably more suitable since async stream notifications are only available on iOS 15 and later:

```Swift
NotificationCenter.default.addObserver(
    forName: NSUbiquitousKeyValueStore.didChangeExternallyNotification,
    object: nil,
    queue: .main
) { [weak self] notification in
    guard let self = self else { return }
    DispatchQueue.main.async {
        self.didChangeExternally(notification: notification)
    }
}
```

Is there a way to store optional enums? For example:

```swift
@CloudStorage(AppStorageKeys.selectedTab) var selectedTab: Tab?

private enum Tab: String {
    case home
    case preferences
}
```

I get error "Type of expression is ambiguous without a type annotation".
